title: Over Five Hundred Graded T206 Cards FS / FT ***
author: Roulette44

posts.post_title: Over Five Hundred Graded T206 Cards FS / FT ***
posts.post_content:
UPDATED 3-4-2018; Newest list of cards is on page 2 of the thread!   :)

Hey all - Joey here!   

I haven't posted too many times, but have bought from or sold to at least 15-20 boardies here.   I've been bigger into comics but started getting really passionate about cards again (T206 in particular).   I use the handle InvestmentGradeKeyComics on ebay, FYI.

As i've upgraded my personal T206 set, i've accumulated lots of doubles and triples.  They've been getting listed (e.g., on ebay) over time, but I realized posting here might help my fellow forumites!  :rolleyes:

I'll both a) paste the list of cards here in the thread and b) attach a txt file you can download.

There's something for everyone here, I think!  There are: 
- Grades from 1 to 6 (with over 200 cards graded 4 or better)
- Many backs (Including Lenox, Hindu, P42, Tolstoi, AB and more!)
- HOFers (
- Errors/Scrap
- PSA and SGC

Please shoot me an email for any interest in seeing scans.   investmentgradekeycomics@gmail.com

Some of these cards are already up on ebay as well, if you'd prefer to look there. 

Finally, feel free to email if you want to get an excel file of these (easier to navigate, sort, etc.)

Payment via paypal is fine.   Wires for larger amounts are cool too.   

In terms of Trade, I have my own want list for T206 (PSA 5.5-7 for the most part).  I'd also like PSA 5s of Plank and Magie Error.   Finally any 1940 Superman GUM (R145) cards in PSA 4 or better might be of interest, or any key comics from the silver or golden age.

Happy Hunting!
Thanks
Joey

Joey's bought a couple items from me, great to deal with.

Man, those are your doubles?  DAMN, your set is smokin'!!

Just had to follow up and say that I had a really exceptional experience buying some of these T206's from Joey.

Got 5 very nice T206's, and considered a good number more.  The cards that arrived were all better than the scans.  

Great communication, a few laughs, and a fair deal on some extremely nice cards.  Thanks!

Thanks for all the interest and great conversation!  Have met several new folks through this process and must say the T206 collectors here are a cool, respectful bunch, i'm glad to have found these boards!

Anyhow, i wanted to provide a quick update.    About 100 of the cards have found new homes, but i also have upgraded more of my own, bringing more for sale to the list!

What follows is an updated list that should be current as of today!  Drop me a line to discuss!  Note that atleast another 100 cards on the list below have been offered to individuals, meaning they could drop off the list at any moment - timestamp of communication denotes who wins in the case of multiple interested buyers.
